thread.title: Lockheed wins $431 mln contract for support work on F-35
thread.title_full: Lockheed wins $431 mln contract for support work on F-35 | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: Lockheed wins $431 mln contract for support work on F-35
text:
WASHINGTON Aug 31 Lockheed Martin Corp has won a contract worth $431 million to provide support equipment and services for the ninth batch of F-35 fighter jets, the Pentagon announced Monday.
The contract covers spare parts, support equipment, hardware and software for the F-35's computerized Autonomic Logistics Information System, full mission simulators and non-recurring engineering services, the Defense Department said in its daily digest of major weapons contracts. (Reporting by Andrea Shalal ; Editing by Andrew Hay)
